defaultAlso of significance is the proposal to turn the Highways Agency into a publicly owned corporation with greater long term funding certainty. The main advantage cited is the potential to achieve £600m of capital efficiency savings; equally 
defaultimportant is the opportunity this will provide for the successor HA to build up better strategic relationships with key industry customers such as ports.
